Robbers who plundered Eshowe Road Traffic Inspectorate offices on Sunday night, stole firearm safes, firearms, rounds of ammunition and car keys with each car's petrol card. According to the police, Eshowe officers received a report of a robbery at the Eshoweâ€™s RTI offices and went to the scene. KZN Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said upon their arrival at the said location, police were met by the security guard. She said the security guard alleged he was accosted by four men with guns who tied him up. Mbele said the men broke into the office where they stole 11 firearm safes, five firearms, 135 rounds of ammunition and 10 vehicle keys with their respective petrol cards before they fled the scene. She said a case of business robbery has been opened at Eshowe SAPS. Eshowe police are appealing to the community to help with any information regarding the robbery. Mbele said those who may be able to assist should contact Eshowe SAPS on 035 473 4237/Crime Stop on 08600 10111 or information can be communicated via the MYSAPS app.